// LANG.md §7.2 (ADR-035): `Type from Expr` carries a type onto a value; where
// the source's type is determinable it MUST match the target. A `number` target
// with a string-literal source is a model error.

//! example

public system S;

public container C for S {
  run(): void {
    n = number from ""
  }
}
